[3] South Carolina (Pickens County)
Date: Fri 23 Mar 2012
Source: WSPA [edited]
http://www2.wspa.com/news/2012/mar/23/two-cases-whooping-cough-confirmed-upstate-ar-3464828/

According to the Pickens County School District, 2 students from the same family have been confirmed with cases of whooping cough. One student is at Pickens Elementary, and the other is at Pickens High. Both students have been treated. Family and close contacts have also been preventatively treated.

The district has been working with state health officials and both schools have been notified. PHS chose to do a parent link and have letters available for extra information.

